message.content:
Fix authentication state display and error handling across the frontend at `/Users/tanishqsingh/Desktop/yash desktop files/projects/outreach-proj/frontend-v2`.

**Problems to fix:**

### 1. Sidebar shows hardcoded "Jordan M." (file: `src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx`)
Currently the bottom of the sidebar has:
```tsx
<div className="sb-item" style={{ marginTop: 4 }}>
  <div style={{ ...gradient avatar... }}>JM</div>
  <span style={{ fontSize: 12 }}>Jordan M.</span>
  ...
</div>
```
Fix: Read actual user info from localStorage. The dev login stores `outreach_token` as a JWT. Decode the payload (base64, middle segment) to get `email`. Show first letter of email as avatar initial, show email truncated. Do this safely — if decoding fails, show "You". Example:
```tsx
function getUserFromToken(): { email: string; initials: string } {
  try {
    const token = localStorage.getItem("outreach_token") ?? "";
    const payload = JSON.parse(atob(token.split(".")[1]));
    const email: string = payload.email ?? "user";
    const initials = email[0].toUpperCase();
    return { email, initials };
  } catch {
    return { email: "You", initials: "U" };
  }
}
```
Call this with `React.useMemo` inside the component and replace the hardcoded values.

Also fix: the sidebar has hardcoded campaign items ("Acme Q2 outbound", "Design leads · NYC", "Enterprise SaaS") with hardcoded counts. Replace these with `{ id: "dashboard", label: "All campaigns", icon: "target", href: "/dashboard" }` as a single item — no fake data.

### 2. Campaign dashboard outreach endpoint errors (file: `src/app/campaign/[id]/dashboard/page.tsx`)
The `listOutreach` call can return 500 if the campaign has no data yet (it's still "draft" or "processing"). The page currently crashes. Fix: wrap the `listOutreach` and `getCampaignStats` calls in separate try/catches so they fail independently. If `listOutreach` fails, show an empty state ("No contacts yet — campaign is still being processed"). If `getCampaignStats` fails, show zeros. Don't let either failure crash the whole page.

### 3. Auth callback page (file: `src/app/auth/callback/page.tsx` — check if it exists)
If it exists, make sure it correctly reads `access_token` from URL params and stores it as `outreach_token` in localStorage, then redirects to `/dashboard`. If the file doesn't exist, create it:
```tsx
"use client";
import React from "react";
import { useRouter, useSearchParams } from "next/navigation";

function AuthCallbackInner() {
  const router = useRouter();
  const params = useSearchParams();
  React.useEffect(() => {
    const token = params.get("access_token");
    if (token) {
      localStorage.setItem("outreach_token", token);
      router.replace("/dashboard");
    } else {
      router.replace("/auth");
    }
  }, [params, router]);
  return <div style={{ height: "100vh", display: "flex", alignItems: "center", justifyContent: "center", background: "var(--bg)", color: "var(--fg)" }}>Signing you in…</div>;
}

export default function AuthCallback() {
  return <React.Suspense fallback={null}><AuthCallbackInner /></React.Suspense>;
}
```

Read all files before editing. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` from the frontend directory to verify no TypeScript errors. Report what you changed and any files created.

